caption.p: The identification of the volatile fraction in Micromeria frivaldszkyana essential oils by using LRI (Linear Retention Index). LRI lib are values reported in FFNSC 3.01 library; LRI exp are obtained experimentally on SLB-5ms column. % MS Sim. represents the similarity between experimental and library spectra. The quantification of flavour and fragrance compounds in Micromeria frivaldszkyana essential oils by GC-FID % area values are the average of three repetitions.

fn.p: * Means followed by the same letter within a row are not significantly different at the 5% level of significance. * A coelution between Piperitone oxide <cis-> and Piperitone on SLB-5ms column. * B coelution between 1,5-di-epi-beta-bourbonene and Elemene <β-> on SLB-5ms column. b the sum of the not identified components.
